-- Akbank Falls to Lowest Since January After Profit Drops 25%
-- B y   B e n j a m i n   H a r v e y
-- 2012-04-30T15:25:42Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-30/akbank-falls-to-lowest-since-january-after-profit-drops-25-.html
Akbank TAS (AKBNK) , the Turkish lender in
which Citigroup Inc. is seeking to reduce its stake from 20
percent to less than 10 percent, slumped to the lowest since
January after saying first-quarter profit fell 25 percent.  The shares dropped 2.7 percent to 6.52 liras at the close
in Istanbul, their lowest since Jan. 25.  First-quarter net income fell to 555.6 million liras ($316
million), according to a statement to the  Istanbul Stock
Exchange  today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Benjamin Harvey in Istanbul at 
 bharvey11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
